Cisco Nexus HyperFabric AI Clusters

Many organizations are looking to simplify deployment and operations across the AI infrastructure through integrated data, compute, software, storage, and high-performance networking. The Cisco Nexus HyperFabric AI cluster solution is designed to simplify deployments for the enterprise with plug-and-play cloud management for AI-native infrastructure.

The Cisco Nexus HyperFabric AI cluster solution combines Cisco AI-native networking with NVIDIA accelerated computing and AI software, and a robust data store. The solution guides organizations through the entire infrastructure lifecycle process, from design to order, deployment, configuration, validation, and continuous operations for AI deployments.

The Cisco Nexus HyperFabric AI cluster comprises the following components:

  • Cisco 6000 series switches for spine and leaf that deliver 400G and 800G Ethernet fabric performance

  • Cisco Optics family of QSFP-DD modules to offer customer choice and deliver super high densities

  • NVIDIA AI Enterprise software to streamline the development of production-grade generative AI workloads

  • NVIDIA NIM inference microservices that accelerate the deployment of foundation models while ensuring data security

  • NVIDIA Tensor Core GPUs that are designed to supercharge generative AI workloads with game-changing performance and memory capabilities

  • NVIDIA BlueField-3 data processing unit DPU processor and BlueField-3 SuperNIC for accelerating AI compute networking, data access, and security workloads

  • The VAST Data Platform, which offers unified storage, a database, and a data-driven function engine built for AI

Cisco Nexus HyperFabric Capabilities

Cisco Nexus HyperFabric is a purpose-built network fabric-as-a-service data center offer. Using a Cisco managed cloud controller, the solution enables customers to easily design, deploy, and manage any number of fabrics, AI-enabled or not, that are located anywhere, spanning primary data centers, colocation facilities, and DC edge sites.

Cisco Nexus HyperFabric reinvents the IT operations lifecycle of the data center by simplifying every step of the process.

Explore the Simplified IT Operations Lifecycle

Click the lifecycle stages to learn how Cisco Nexus HyperFabric simplifies each stage.

SDN Integration with Cisco Nexus HyperFabric AI Clusters

Cisco Nexus HyperFabric AI clusters integrate seamlessly with Software-Defined Networking (SDN) to enhance the agility, scalability, and efficiency of AI workloads.

SDN provides centralized network management and orchestration, allowing adjustments to network configurations in real-time. Cisco Nexus HyperFabric is a cloud-based controller, offering fabric-as-a-service, which is a single point of administration for all fabrics regardless of location. This capability helps with maintaining the high-performance demands of AI applications in which uninterrupted data flow between nodes and data centers is vital.

SDN enhances the scalability of Cisco Nexus HyperFabric by allowing dynamic adjustments to network resources, ensuring the infrastructure can meet growing demands without compromising performance. Also, advanced traffic management capabilities with SDN enable intelligent routing that reduces latency and improves the overall performance of the AI training and inference processes.

In addition to performance improvements, SDN strengthens the security of Cisco Nexus HyperFabric by enabling consistent security policies and real-time threat mitigation across the network. The integration of SDN also extends Cisco Nexus HyperFabricâ€™s capabilities to cloud and edge environments, supporting seamless operations in distributed AI applications.
